  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mama en Pikin Welbodi Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will take place in five of the most remote chiefdoms in Bombali and Karene, Northern Sierra Leone. It will
support 115 Community Health Workers to identify and refer approximately 450 malnourished children under five,
500 unvaccinated children, and 4,500 pregnant women to health services, especially those in households living with
disability. These beneficiaries will benefit from project health/nutrition education activities and access to improved
health/nutrition services and outreaches. 900 target households with particularly vulnerable pregnant mothers and or
vulnerable children will also be further supported to establish low-cost home gardens and poultry/sheep/goat pass-on
schemes. This will contribute to improved health and nutrition of pregnant women and children under five by reducing
incidences of under- and malnutrition by improving community feeding and hygiene practices and improving the
health system&#x2019;s capacity to deliver quality health and nutrition services.</narrative>
  </description>
